Why am I telling you about this?

. . .

1) Models are about more than just prediction; they enable us to **make sense of patterns in data** and **measure things we care about**.

. . .

2) The best work and the best predictions tend to come from **really trying to understand the thing you are predicting**.

---

To that end, let's talk about the CFB Playoff.

. . .

How do you predict the college football playoff? You use your measures of team performance to simulate how the playoff might unfold. You do this thousands of times.

. . .

I ran my first simulations on the eve of the playoff. I will admit, I was suspicious of the results and my own model.

